The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Cricketers remember the victims
                                                   Cricketers remember the victims
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The players and support staff of both the India and New Zealand teams, along with the match officials, observed a minutes silence before the start of the second one-day International in Wellington as a mark of respect for the victims of the terror attack on the Sri Lankan team in Lahore.         
	The gesture was also repeated before the start of the two Test matches  second Test between South Africa and Australia in Durban and the fifth between West Indies and England in Port of Spain.         
	Players and officials also wore black armbands on the first day of each Tests and the ODI.         
	The minutes silence is also to be observed during the opening matches of the ICC Womens World Cup on Saturday.         
	The attack in Lahore on Tuesday left eight people dead and several others injured.                                                                                                                       
